#
# @summary Interpreter for 'helpenv <name> <location>' (documentation display)
# @default cat
# @values cat | cut -b3- | sh
# @see VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_helpenv0
# @see VPN_SWITCH_TERMINAL_INTERPRETER
#
# Hard, arity-specific interpreter for the helpenv documentation renderer.
#
# This is set explicitly rather than inheriting VPN_SWITCH_TERMINAL_INTERPRETER
# on purpose: that global terminal default is a safety-first setting ("cat", show
# don't run) that most users flip to "sh" for auto-execution. helpenv must ALWAYS
# display its output and never execute it, or the help system would break the
# moment a user opts into "sh". The arity-specific name sits at the top of the
# interpreter resolution order and shadows the class default, so this can never
# be changed as collateral damage from tuning the global terminal interpreter.
#
# @internal
# Mirrors how 'help' pins VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_help=cat, but arity-specific
# (helpenv0/helpenv2) because helpenv1 is a combinator that needs the re-dispatch
# interpreter — an arity-agnostic VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_helpenv would wrongly
# capture it.
